{
  "texts": [
    "where h (l-1) denotes the input of layer l, and h ′(l) represents the output of layer l after passing through the multi-head attention mechanism module, which is also the input of the position pre-encoding module for layer l.",
    "Distances between nodes in complex networks often vary.",
    "The more distant nodes frequently represent the network's edges and the connections between different components, and they can provide crucial information about the network as a whole.",
    "GAT for feature update among first-order neighbors Both GAT and Transformer incorporate self-attention mechanisms.",
    "One distinction lies in the ability of the Transformer technique to acquire global node information, whereas the GAT method concentrates solely on the first-order neighbor nodes of the given nodes."
  ]
}